IsUTF8 version 0.2
==================

The IsUTF8 modules provides a simple function to check if some given
string contains at least one UTF8 character sequence.  If you're looking
for something like UTF8 autodetection, then it's for you :)

It has smaller footprint than other Encode:: packages.

INSTALLATION

To install this module type the following:

   perl Makefile.PL

or
   perl Makefile.PL PREFIX=$HOME

	But being useful at this place ($HOME) you've to point your Perl
	@INC to your $HOME later. E.g. by setting the environment
	variable PERL5LIB to "$HOME/share/perl".


   make
   make test
   make install

DEPENDENCIES

This module does not require other modules and libraries.


